productContent.fullTitle: Nike Air Max 97 JDI Men's Shoe
productContent.title: Nike Air Max 97 JDI
productContent.subtitle: Men's Shoe
productContent.description:
SLEEK COMFORT


The Nike Air Max 97 shook up the running world with its revolutionary full-length Nike Air unit. The Nike Air Max 97 JDI Men's Shoe remasters the original design with a synthetic and textile construction for a lighter feel and a sleeker look.


Product Features

  • Synthetic leather, synthetic and textile construction
  • Foam sole with Max Air cushioning
  • Rubber outsole
  • Reflective details help you stand out

    • Air Max 97 Origins

    Nike's revolutionary Air-Sole unit made its way into Nike footwear in 1978. In 1987, the Nike Air Max 1 debuted with visible air in its heel, allowing fans more than just the feel of Air-Sole comfort—suddenly they could see it. Two years after the Nike Air Max 95 brought visible air to the forefoot, the Nike Air Max 97 arrived with the very first full-length unit. The shoe made a huge splash in the running world, as anticipated by its ripple-effect design lines. It's still making waves over two decades later.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13
properties.title: AIR JORDAN XIII
properties.subtitle: LOVE THE GAME

properties.body: This past weekend, New York City celebrated the upcoming return of the iconic Air Jordan XIII White/True Red/Black. One of the original colorways from Michael Jordan’s playing days, the shoe has been a staple in sneaker culture since the ‘90s.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: In honor of the 20-year anniversary of the shoe’s debut and its legendary appearance on the big screen, Jordan Brand hosted a pop-up on July 28th near Coney Island’s iconic boardwalk.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: Sneaker customizer NAMXKEEL created one-of-one versions of the Air Jordan XIII using his signature dipping technique. Each shoe was customized in one of three ice cream flavor-inspired colors to create a unique alteration inspired by the Coney Island boardwalk treat.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: Visitors were challenged to show off their game as they participated in on-court basketball activities. Three of New York City’s homegrown streetball stars served as trainers and opponents for a 3-point contest and one-on-one matches.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: The Air Jordan XIII White/True Red/Black releases globally August 4th on SNKRS and at select retailers.

CLASSIC COMFORT


The Nike Air Max 95 made its mark as the first shoe to include visible Nike Air cushioning in the forefoot. The Nike Air Max 95 OG MC SP Men's Shoe energizes the iconic design with updated materials in a variety of textures and accents.

    Nike's revolutionary Air-Sole unit made its way into Nike footwear in 1978. In 1987, the Nike Air Max 1 debuted with visible air in its heel, allowing fans more than just the feel of Air-Sole comfort—suddenly they could see it. Air reached a new milestone in 1995, when the Nike Air Max 95 opened more windows, this time in the forefoot. Known as much for its innovation as for its design lines inspired by human anatomy, the Nike Air Max 95 became a classic the moment it dropped.

properties.subtitle: AIR JORDAN X
properties.body: Look familiar? Back in April, attendees of the 2018 Jordan Brand Classic were treated to an Air Jordan X exclusive. For the first time in the X's history, the shoe featured the cement speckle pattern made popular by the Air Jordan IV. Now the rest of the public has its chance. With a full leather construction and colors inspired by the JBC design, the latest colorway goes back for cement-splattered seconds.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13
properties.title: AIR JORDAN XIII
properties.subtitle: LOVE THE GAME

properties.body: This past weekend, New York City celebrated the upcoming return of the iconic Air Jordan XIII White/True Red/Black. One of the original colorways from Michael Jordan’s playing days, the shoe has been a staple in sneaker culture since the ‘90s.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: In honor of the 20-year anniversary of the shoe’s debut and its legendary appearance on the big screen, Jordan Brand hosted a pop-up on July 28th near Coney Island’s iconic boardwalk.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: Sneaker customizer NAMXKEEL created one-of-one versions of the Air Jordan XIII using his signature dipping technique. Each shoe was customized in one of three ice cream flavor-inspired colors to create a unique alteration inspired by the Coney Island boardwalk treat.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: Visitors were challenged to show off their game as they participated in on-court basketball activities. Three of New York City’s homegrown streetball stars served as trainers and opponents for a 3-point contest and one-on-one matches.

properties.altText: Love The Game: Air Jordan 13

properties.body: The Air Jordan XIII White/True Red/Black releases globally August 4th on SNKRS and at select retailers.

The Nike Air Max 95 made its mark as the first shoe to include visible Nike Air cushioning in the forefoot. The Nike Air Max 95 OG MC SP Men's Shoe energizes the iconic design with updated materials in a variety of textures and accents.

    • Air Max 95 Origins

    Nike's revolutionary Air-Sole unit made its way into Nike footwear in 1978. In 1987, the Nike Air Max 1 debuted with visible air in its heel, allowing fans more than just the feel of Air-Sole comfort—suddenly they could see it. Air reached a new milestone in 1995, when the Nike Air Max 95 opened more windows, this time in the forefoot. Known as much for its innovation as for its design lines inspired by human anatomy, the Nike Air Max 95 became a classic the moment it dropped.

properties.subtitle: AIR JORDAN X
properties.body: Look familiar? Back in April, attendees of the 2018 Jordan Brand Classic were treated to an Air Jordan X exclusive. For the first time in the X's history, the shoe featured the cement speckle pattern made popular by the Air Jordan IV. Now the rest of the public has its chance. With a full leather construction and colors inspired by the JBC design, the latest colorway goes back for cement-splattered seconds.
